CatDescriptText: Mrs. Lucille Wooden, 2401 Waring Court, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 15, 1958, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think common-law marriage should be outlawed?" answer reads: "I think it should. In my opinion, what's the use of having legal marriages?  America's morals are going down to its lowest point.  Why make them any lower?"
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Lucille Wooden, wearing light colored coat with plaid collar, holding gloves and paper bag, standing in front of brick wall
